    About this hotel

    Offering views of the Atlas Mountains, this upscale riad within the walls of the medina is 2 km from traditional entertainment and dining at Jama El Fna, the city's buzzy main square. Marrakesh Menara Airport is 7 km away.

    Check-in time: 2:00 PM
    Check-out time: 12:00 PM

    Therese Overstedt3 months ago on Google
    5/5
    We had an absolute wonderful stay here in July 2022 for 4 nights. This Riad takes service to a new level. Every single staff delivers a high level of service which is unique for even a luxury hotel. We really enjoyed the feeling of almost 
    We had an absolute wonderful stay here in July 2022 for 4 nights. This Riad takes service to a new level. Every single staff delivers a high level of service which is unique for even a luxury hotel. We really enjoyed the feeling of almost having the place to ourselves. There are plenty of small lounge areas so you feel very private. You can have your meals wherever you want but sitting on the roof terrace is wonderful when the sun sets. The breakfast is amazing with fresh fruits, pastries, bread and then whatever else you want to pick from a menu at no extra cost. You can also order coffee and water at no cost throughout the day. We also had fruit and cookies in our room every day. It's a small thing but very nice!
    The staff will help you with whatever you need and there is always someone at hand to escort you in the labyrinth of the medina but you'll soon get the hang of it. We never felt scared walking through the small alleys, even at night, but it would be tricky if you got lost. Our phones didn't work well but we were given a mobile phone by the hotel so we could get in contact with them whenever we were out and wanted to be picked up. They also arranged for taxis when we needed (standard fixed rate for rides in central Marrakesh seemed to be 5).
    We wanted to come back to this Riad while we were in Morocco but changed our plans but we will definitely stay here again next time we visit. Million thanks to the entire staff!

    Medina

    Hammam bath houses and covered spice and textile souks line the maze of cobblestoned lanes in the Medina, which occupies Marrakeshs original fortified citadel. At night, Jemaa el-Fna square teems with snake charmers, folk dancers, and street food vendors serving all manner of food. Bahia Palace and Le Jardin Secret are 19th-century complexes open to the public, with ornate courtyards, mosaics, and gardens.

    About this hotel

    Offering views of the Atlas Mountains, this upscale riad within the walls of the medina is 2 km from traditional entertainment and dining at Jama El Fna, the city's buzzy main square. Marrakesh Menara Airport is 7 km away.

    Refined rooms with traditional decor offer Wi-Fi, minifridges, safes and loaner phones, plus sofas. Suites add living areas. Some have fireplaces and/or balconies.

    Breakfast is available. There's also an upmarket restaurant with rooftop and interior courtyard dining areas. Other amenities include an outdoor pool, a spa, a hammam and guided area tours. Kids age 12 and over are welcome. Minimum-stay rules apply.
